-- v0.2 observations:
--
-- ⊢= expression language compliance:
--   compare-steps uses: subtraction (valid ⊢= arithmetic)
--   verdict uses: if/then/else, and, not, comparison (all valid ⊢= primitives)
--   R16 had these judgments in a single "compare" cell with ⊢= bodies containing
--   "original-output and optimized-output address the same question with equivalent
--   factual content" — this is a semantic judgment, NOT a valid ⊢= expression.
--   R17 splits the compare cell: compare-semantics (soft, ∴) handles the semantic
--   judgment, compare-steps (hard, ⊢=) handles arithmetic, verdict (hard, ⊢=) handles
--   the deterministic classification. The crystallization boundary is now correct.
--
-- ⊢∘ target oracles (aspirational):
--   propose-optimization's oracles (valid syntax, shorter text, changes described)
--   were noted as aspirational during frame 3. Under v0.2, they serve as feedback
--   signals to the ⊢∘ loop but do not independently gate freezing. The ⊢∘ until
--   condition (semantics-preserved and step-delta >= 0) is the actual gate.
